          <text>
                    <body>
                              <pb n="1"/>
                              <p>
                                        <add>דע"ה פה ב??? אור ליום ד י"ט מכתבי תריב</add>
                              </p>
                              <p>Married by the—<persName role="author">Isaac M.
                                        Slatky</persName><lb/> on the <date><sic>18. Menachim <hi
                                                  rend="underline">5;612</hi></sic> (Augt. 3D <hi
                                                  rend="underline">1852</hi></date><lb/>
                                        <persName>Mr Isaac Michael</persName> to <persName>Mrs<lb/>
                                                  Hannah Tobias</persName> Both of the City
                                                  <placeName><sic>St Luis</sic><lb/>
                                                  Miss</placeName><lb/>
                                        <add>לתו</add></p>
                              <p rend="indent(9)">
                                        <persName role="author">Isaac. M. Slatky</persName>
                              </p>
                              <p rend="indent(8)">
                                        <placeName>No 134 Elliott St. Buffalo N. Y.</placeName>
                              </p>
                              <p>
                                        <add>לאהובי רעי ועמיתי ה"ה האלוף המושלם בכל מעלה כמר ר' יצחק
                                                  לעדר מר אוכי"ח</add>
                              </p>
                              <pb n="2"/>
                              <p>Revd.</p>
                              <p rend="indent(1)">
                                        <addressee>Isaac Leeser</addressee>
                              </p>
                              <p rend="indent(1)">Editor of the Occident</p>
                              <p rend="indent(2)">
                                        <placeName>Philadelphia</placeName>
                              </p>
                              <p>
                                        <hi rend="underline">paid</hi>
                              </p>
                              <pb n="3"/>
                              <p rend="align(right)"><placeName>Buffalo</placeName>, <date>Tuesday
                                                  evening, 13<hi rend="sup">th</hi> Ab,
                                        5612</date></p>
                              <p>To my trusted friend, the very learned and accomplished<lb/>
                                        <addressee>Rabbi Isaac Leeser</addressee>, long may he live,
                                        Amen.</p>
                              <p>My beloved, my friend,</p>
                              <p rend="indent(1)">At this time I shall not write at length, for I am
                                        heavy<lb/> of speech and of tongue, and am not able to speak
                                        the Hebrew language<lb/> in its purity. But, I come to let
                                        you know that I have received a<lb/> brief letter from your
                                        High Honor, by the hand of <persName>Mr.
                                                  Bernheimer.</persName><lb/> He told me that I
                                        really have no need of this trouble of going from<lb/> house
                                        to house, and this way and that, to seek for subscribers
                                        to<lb/> the Bible which is to be translated into English by
                                        your worthy self.<lb/> I, therefore, write this letter to
                                        Your Worthiness to let you know<lb/> that I, the least in
                                        the tribes of <placeName>Israel</placeName>, am ready
                                        to<lb/> take from Your Honor one set, the price of which I
                                        shall send after<lb/> the <date>Rosh ha-shana</date> that is
                                        approaching. I also desire a prayer book<lb/> for holidays
                                        of the Polish ritual, if you have one. If so, please<lb/>
                                        let me know before the <date>Rosh Hodesh of Ellul</date>
                                        coming.</p>
                              <p rend="indent(1)">In passing I cannot refrain to give you a small
                                        bit<lb/> of news to be included in the Occident of the
                                        coming month;—</p>
                              <p rend="indent(1)">“Married by the __<persName role="author">Isaac M.
                                                  Slatky</persName> on the <date>18 Menahim*
                                                  5;612<lb/> ( August 3d 1852)</date>
                                        <persName>Mr. Isaac Michael</persName> to <persName>Mrs.
                                                  Hannah Tobias</persName>, both<lb/> of the City of
                                                  <placeName>St. Louis Miss.</placeName></p>
                              <p rend="indent(1)">I have no further news.</p>
                              <p rend="indent(1)">He who seeks his peoples welfare, and who hopes
                                        for<lb/> your answer,</p>
                              <p rend="indent(8)">
                                        <persName role="author">Isaac Slatkin</persName>
                              </p>
                              <p rend="indent(6)">Address — <placeName>134 Ellicott St., Buffalo N.
                                                  Y.</placeName></p>
                              <p>I hope that Your High Honor will send me a letter without any
                                        delay.</p>
                              <p>flowery Hebrew—tis none too pure</p>
                              <p>* <date>Ab</date></p>
                    </body>
